#ThankYouEveryDAY6 for your hard work, thank you for bringing me and my best friend lina together, thank you for always giving us a new concept to look forward to, thank you for helping me through tough times, and thank you for bringing mydays together like a family. we love you!
so, day6, thank you. thank you for everything. and the show must go on. love, mydays.

thank you for working so hard this past year, and for showing us that an artist can never release a bad song, even over the period of a month. every single song of everyday6, including the b-sides, have been spectacular. i don’t know how you guys do it, honestly.

your music has been one of my driving forces these past six months. from my lowest lows to my highest highs, your music has always been there. thank you thank you thank you. i can now express in words how much your music has helped me and so many others.

but, although i was fairly new to your music, mydays quickly accepted me as their family and weve spent the past six months together. one huge, loving family. thank you, day6, for creating this space where we all can just enjoy the music.

my open letter to day6 ( @Jae_Day6 ): first off, thank you. thank you for putting so much hard work, so much effort and so much energy into everyday6. when i first started stanning right before the July comeback, ill be honest, i had no clue what was happening.
